 Connect to the Digital Editions of the Bomb The digital yearbooks are hosted at the Internet Archive  The list will appear in reverse chronological order  beginning with the most recent volume You can choose from a variety of formats  browse and search a volume by choosing the  read online  option  download the PDF  or access other formats  About the Digitization Project  This exciting project was made possible through the LYRASIS Mass Digitization Collaborative   a Sloan Foundation grant subsidized program that has made digitization easy and affordable for libraries and cultural institutions across the country Through the Collaborative s partnership with the Internet Archive  all items were scanned from cover to cover and in full color Colleges and universities throughout Virginia and around the country have participated in the yearbook digitization project  For this project  the original printed editions of the yearbook were scanned in the summer of 2010  About the Yearbook  Known as The Bomb  the yearbook was first published in 1885  After a nine year hiatus  it has been published continuously since 1895  with the exception of 1945   1946   Disclaimer  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu The VMI Bomb  Yearbook  Online   Digital Access from the VMI Archives  skip to content All Collections Limit to Historical Rosters Limit to Photographs VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About