hrough the LYRASIS Mass Digitization Collaborative   a Sloan Foundation grant subsidized program that has made digitization easy and affordable for libraries and cultural institutions across the country Through the Collaborative s partnership with the Internet Archive  all items were scanned from cover to cover and in full color Colleges and universities throughout Virginia and around the country have participated in the yearbook digitization project  For this project  the original printed editions of the yearbook were scanned in the summer of 2010  About the Yearbook  Known as The Bomb  the yearbook was first published in 1885  After a nine year hiatus  it has been published continuously since 1895  with the exception of 1945   1946   Disclaimer Archives Home Digital Collections Digital Collections Site Cadet Newspaper The Bomb  Yearbook  Archives Online Catalog Quick Info  FAQs Civil War   New Market Stonewall Jackson Genealogy   Alumni Photos   Portraits Letters  Diaries  Manuscripts Digital Exhibits Home Military Oral History VMI Records Records Management About the Archives Mary Laura Kludy Archives Assistant Ph   540  464 7516 Fax   540  464 7089 archives vmi edu Preston Library Lexington  Virginia 24450 Hours   Visitor Info Archives Home Digital Collections Digital Collections Site Cadet Newspaper The Bomb  Yearbook  Archives Online Catalog Quick Info  FAQs Civil War   New Market Stonewall Jackson Genealogy   Alumni Photos   Portraits Letters  Diaries  Manuscripts Digital Exhibits Home Military Oral History VMI Records Records Management About the Archives Mary Laura Kludy Archives Assistant Ph   540  464 7516 Fax   540  464 7089 archives vmi edu Preston Library Lexington  Virginia 24450 Hours   Visitor Info Archives Home Digital Collections Digital Collections Site Cadet Newspaper The Bomb  Yearbook  Archives Online Catalog Quick Info  FAQs Civil War   New Market Stonewall Jackson Genealogy   Alumni Photos   Portraits Letters  Diaries  Manuscripts Digital Ex